01:04:38.930 --> 01:04:41.500
told me I was too
cute for a black girl.

01:04:41.500 --> 01:04:44.280
Like he forgot my
skin wasn't passed

01:04:44.280 --> 01:04:46.030
down by solid kings
and beautiful queens.

01:04:46.030 --> 01:04:49.930
Like he forgot my skin wasn't a
symbol for the metal in my back,

01:04:49.930 --> 01:04:51.990
the sass in my hips,
the ocean in throat.

01:04:51.990 --> 01:04:55.850
This boy forgot I was forgotten
letters sent by my father,

01:04:55.850 --> 01:04:57.970
stamped with the year 2000.

01:04:57.970 --> 01:05:01.710
He forgot I was a silver spoon
scooped with chocolate kisses.

01:05:01.710 --> 01:05:03.460
He missed my black privilege

01:05:03.460 --> 01:05:05.420
to say I lived past
my days of puberty.

01:05:05.420 --> 01:05:08.420
So I shall not apologize for
wearing this black hoodie

01:05:08.420 --> 01:05:11.240
on my black skin, and shout
to Trayvon Martin for dying

01:05:11.240 --> 01:05:14.940
for my sins, the skin lost
in the horizons of the sun,

01:05:14.940 --> 01:05:20.140
my skin lifted hand, swayed hips
and afro baby blues, our skin.

01:05:20.140 --> 01:05:23.250
Baby, this kind of blackness
runs through our veins,

01:05:23.250 --> 01:05:26.850
roots so deep call us the
tree of life, call me black,

01:05:26.850 --> 01:05:31.270
call me oppression, call
me obituary, call me quick,

01:05:31.270 --> 01:05:34.490
call me insane, call me the
black girl without a brain.

01:05:34.490 --> 01:05:36.830
But if you want me to be
anything out of this range,

01:05:36.830 --> 01:05:38.350
then you can keep the change.

01:05:38.350 --> 01:05:40.150
Thank you.

01:05:40.150 --> 01:05:54.040
