01:07:28.050 --> 01:07:31.020
&gt;&gt; A letter to the
baby I aborted.

01:07:33.630 --> 01:07:38.410
What was I supposed to do
when you asked who Baba is?

01:07:38.410 --> 01:07:40.290
What would I do then?

01:07:40.290 --> 01:07:43.920
Would I tell you the only
time I saw him he reeked

01:07:43.920 --> 01:07:47.260
of cigarette butts
lit out by moonshine,

01:07:47.260 --> 01:07:50.630
threw $11 to my feet before
abandoning this corpse

01:07:50.630 --> 01:07:53.850
on the edge of 17th Street.

01:07:53.850 --> 01:07:58.540
I miss you, today more than
I missed you yesterday.

01:07:58.540 --> 01:08:01.690
What am I supposed to
fill the empty space with?

01:08:01.690 --> 01:08:04.420
How am I supposed to empty
your fragments twisted

01:08:04.420 --> 01:08:06.280
into lumps throughout my soul,

01:08:06.280 --> 01:08:10.320
the words "I am" are
slowly becoming "I was,"

01:08:10.320 --> 01:08:13.150
slowly becoming "we were."

01:08:13.150 --> 01:08:16.940
I've shattered my glass
heart back into loneliness,

01:08:16.940 --> 01:08:20.630
cut my fingers trying to
jigsaw-puzzle us back together.

01:08:20.630 --> 01:08:22.840
And what was I supposed to do?

01:08:22.840 --> 01:08:24.190
What if you had his eyes?

01:08:24.190 --> 01:08:28.290
What if every time
I looked at you,

01:08:28.290 --> 01:08:31.700
I'd watch your eyes unearth
all the wrong parts of me,

01:08:31.700 --> 01:08:35.230
unearth all the shoved screams
from the basement of my belly,

01:08:35.230 --> 01:08:37.850
the puncturing pain
piercing my body,

01:08:37.850 --> 01:08:43.690
remembering how he left every
frozen muscle in me burning.

01:08:43.690 --> 01:08:47.190
What if you were the
spitting image of your father?

01:08:47.190 --> 01:08:52.230
What if every time we
locked eyes, I saw him?

01:08:52.230 --> 01:08:54.960
What if you had his smile?

01:08:54.960 --> 01:08:58.650
Every time we'd laugh I'd
hear his contempt echoing

01:08:58.650 --> 01:09:00.610
in the empty aches of my womb.

01:09:00.610 --> 01:09:02.620
And they say blood is
thicker than water,

01:09:02.620 --> 01:09:05.540
but blood is never thicker
than my fetus slaughtered.

01:09:05.540 --> 01:09:08.510
Why can't water flood
the graveyard of my body,

01:09:08.510 --> 01:09:11.460
wash away the sins
on your tombstone?

01:09:11.460 --> 01:09:16.980
And here I am, planning
the funeral

01:09:16.980 --> 01:09:19.610
for a child that
was never alive.

01:09:19.610 --> 01:09:25.450
Is this missing you, or
the emptiness you fill?

01:09:25.450 --> 01:09:28.830
Is this love, or guilt?

01:09:28.830 --> 01:09:33.710
Only heard you singing in
the soft hums of cold wind,

01:09:33.710 --> 01:09:36.510
never heard your prayers.

01:09:36.510 --> 01:09:39.450
Only felt your hands
slipping from the monkey bar

01:09:39.450 --> 01:09:45.290
of my ribcage, never fisting
around mommy's finger.

01:09:45.290 --> 01:09:47.450
And every time I
watch the sunset,

01:09:47.450 --> 01:09:52.420
I know what would have
been your favorite color.

01:09:52.420 --> 01:09:54.930
And every time I see myself,

01:09:54.930 --> 01:09:58.350
I know what you were
supposed to look like.

01:09:58.350 --> 01:10:01.430
You were supposed
to have my smile.

01:10:01.430 --> 01:10:06.660
You were supposed to be the
spitting image of your mother,

01:10:08.490 --> 01:10:13.910
because you were going to
teach me to love myself,

01:10:13.910 --> 01:10:16.510
because I would have loved you.

01:10:16.510 --> 01:10:48.150
[ Cheering and Applause ]

