01:17:33.110 --> 01:17:35.650
&gt;&gt; Prom night 2017!

01:17:35.650 --> 01:17:37.180
Prom night 2017!

01:17:37.180 --> 01:17:41.310
I'm taking the lint from
the inside of my pockets.

01:17:41.310 --> 01:17:44.700
And I'm taking the
middle-school snowstorm.

01:17:44.700 --> 01:17:46.960
And I'm taking the squeak of
my kicks through the hall.

01:17:46.960 --> 01:17:49.090
Yo, I'm taking the Dean's List.

01:17:49.090 --> 01:17:51.070
Though I was never on it.

01:17:51.070 --> 01:17:53.640
And -- and I'm taking
the awards cabinet.

01:17:53.640 --> 01:17:54.960
Though I was never in it.

01:17:54.960 --> 01:17:56.680
And I'm taking a
bottle of Sprite,

01:17:56.680 --> 01:18:00.430
and I'm gonna be caressing
its curves, like I'm halfway

01:18:00.430 --> 01:18:02.400
through an all-nighter
with less than half

01:18:02.400 --> 01:18:03.870
of the necessary word count.

01:18:03.870 --> 01:18:09.700
I'm taking Blaziken,
Abomasnow and Piplup.

01:18:09.700 --> 01:18:11.000
&gt;&gt; What?

01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:12.300
&gt;&gt; What?

01:18:12.300 --> 01:18:13.600
&gt;&gt; What?

01:18:13.600 --> 01:18:14.900
&gt;&gt; Yes, I said Piplup.

01:18:14.900 --> 01:18:16.680
PokeChat me with small talk
is an HM, and I'll be there

01:18:16.680 --> 01:18:18.250
with every show I
ever binge-watched

01:18:18.250 --> 01:18:19.550
when I was supposed
to be breaking

01:18:19.550 --> 01:18:20.850
down quadratic equations.

01:18:20.850 --> 01:18:23.140
I'm taking every
hole in my bookbag.

01:18:23.140 --> 01:18:29.590
I'm taking every hole and every
pair of sneakers I've ever had.

01:18:29.590 --> 01:18:31.310
I have so many holes.

01:18:31.310 --> 01:18:36.360
You'd have thought me
by now an empty man.

01:18:36.360 --> 01:18:40.550
I fill my body up with
my voice some days just

01:18:40.550 --> 01:18:43.360
to remind myself what I
have left to hold on to.

01:18:43.360 --> 01:18:51.570
And prom night 2017,
I arrived alone.

01:18:51.570 --> 01:18:56.470
Fear lacing the inside
of my collar,

01:18:56.470 --> 01:19:00.170
standing like a last-second
decision waiting

01:19:00.170 --> 01:19:02.250
to shrink back into oblivion.

01:19:02.250 --> 01:19:06.540
But then I see my friends.

01:19:06.540 --> 01:19:10.260
And you'd have thought them
lighthouses the way they waved,

01:19:10.260 --> 01:19:11.770
see?

01:19:11.770 --> 01:19:15.780
High school was a hurricane.

01:19:15.780 --> 01:19:19.720
And we were always
caught standing outside.

01:19:20.740 --> 01:19:22.480
They still make me smile,

01:19:22.480 --> 01:19:25.740
like this is just
another Saturday night.

01:19:25.740 --> 01:19:32.170
And after the music ends,
after we step back outside

01:19:32.170 --> 01:19:33.890
into the cool mouth of
night and make peace

01:19:33.890 --> 01:19:35.870
with our toes stuffed
inside these dress shoes

01:19:35.870 --> 01:19:40.940
and our laughter, like a
dandelion finding the slivers

01:19:40.940 --> 01:19:45.900
of light, finding its way into
every corner of every eye in us,

01:19:45.900 --> 01:19:48.880
a flock of smiles
breaking fly for winter,

01:19:48.880 --> 01:19:53.270
band of black beardless bandits
come to steal the star shine,

01:19:53.270 --> 01:19:56.290
back room bootleg binge
watchmen open our jackets

01:19:56.290 --> 01:19:59.010
like we're trying to let the
whole world inside our part.

01:19:59.010 --> 01:20:01.560
After the music ends, after
the dance floor clears

01:20:01.560 --> 01:20:03.700
like a holiday tabletop,
you find your forehead wet

01:20:03.700 --> 01:20:05.050
with whatever your
footwork managed to kick up.

01:20:05.050 --> 01:20:08.140
The magic dissolved means the
house lights, the doors open

01:20:08.140 --> 01:20:09.440
and let all that stank out.

01:20:09.440 --> 01:20:12.530
We step up, come from out of the
cut again, and this is our part,

01:20:12.530 --> 01:20:15.430
plays like PlayStation
and school bell,

01:20:15.430 --> 01:20:17.510
